but I'm leaning towards the latter,

84
00:03:49,308 --> 00:03:52,869
and I'm going to go on a limb here and state that I think that the interest is definitely there.

85
00:03:53,869 --> 00:03:59,131
I personally found it way easier to convince older adults in my own research to play the VR games

86
00:03:59,551 --> 00:04:01,312
than that it was for them to play the regular games,

87
00:04:01,352 --> 00:04:02,612
and I've been doing this for a couple of years

88
00:04:03,872 --> 00:04:06,733
for reasons such as folks, you know, having seen it on television,

89
00:04:06,753 --> 00:04:10,214
or they might have seen VR ages ago and wanted to see how it evolved,

90
00:04:10,334 --> 00:04:13,095
or a lot of people just wanted to impress their grandkids and so on.

91
00:04:13,655 --> 00:04:17,997
So that's one reason why I think that there's definitely an initial interest for VR games there.

92
00:04:18,517 --> 00:04:22,459
A second reason is a report by Slice Intelligence that I saw.

93
00:04:22,759 --> 00:04:25,220
These guys are actually sponsoring the GDC and have a booth here as well.

94
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:30,302
And they had a sample of 70,000 buyers of PokÃ©mon GO virtual goods.

95
